comments: Sung by the characters "Rudy" and "Dixie Dugan", backed by a chorus. At one performance, audience member Al Jolson rose and sang the song while his then-wife Ruby Keeler danced on stage. This proved to be a popular stunt, so Jolson was hired to continue singing from the audience in further performances.

D' Natural Blues
comments: Paul Williams heard Lucky Millinder and His Orchestra perform "D' Natural Blues" and decided to perform this song too. He called it "The Huckle-Buck". The reactions turned out to be very positive and he decided to record it (December 15th, 1948). Lucky Millinder recorded it a few weeks later (beginning of January 1949), but it was his band's song and he performed it first.
